declarations.comments: Wraps a lens into a field, without HTML label
declarations.title: field

declarations.comments:
Create a field with a lens and a function that wraps around the <input> element.
For example typical form would wrap <input> with a <label> tag.
See fieldWithLabel for example.
declarations.title: fieldWrapped

declarations.comments:
Create a field with a lens and a HTML element.
The element will be added in front of the <input> element,
inside the <label> tag.
declarations.title: fieldWithLabel

declarations.comments: Create a field with a lens and a String that is used as the label.
declarations.title: fieldWithText

declarations.comments:
Add a condition to the field.
If the condition does not match, the field won't be updated.
declarations.title: withPred

declarations.comments: Turns fields into the form HTML.
declarations.title: form
